<LP>
   BEVERLY ENTERPRISES Inc. (Fort Smith, Ark.) -- said it is
offering $40 million of 9% convertible subordinated
debentures due Aug. 15, 2000. Each debenture is convertible
into common stock at an initial conversion price of $6.45 a
share. The offering was managed by Merrill Lynch Capital
Markets and Stephens Inc. The company said it intends to use
the net proceeds to repay debt and satisfy other obligations
under a restructuring agreement. The company operates nursing
facilities, pharmacies and retirement homes.
